The main channel to monitor when storms approach is TG 21204 on the MDICE TRS. Also worth monitoring is the Champaign County ARES spotter channel 444.100 (162.2). Since 444.100 is used for other purposes during regular weather, it is best to lock it out in your scanner until the weather turns severe. 155.040 (131.8) and 155.115 (131.8) are no longer used for weather spotting purposes.
